        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:11PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 111 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Sierra Blanca, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sierra Blanca, Indian Hot Springs, Frenchman Canyon, Big Box, and
Little Box.

This includes Interstate 10 in Texas between mile markers 109 and
110.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
